            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-31789-libssl1.1",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-31789 low vulnerability for libssl1.1 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: Converting an excessively large OCTET STRING value to a hexadecimal string leads to a heap buffer overflow on 32 bit platforms.  Impact summary: A heap buffer overflow may lead to a crash or possibly an attacker controlled code execution or other undefined behavior.  If an attacker can supply a crafted X.509 certificate with an excessively large OCTET STRING value in extensions such as the Subject Key Identifier (SKID) or Authority Key Identifier (AKID) which are being converted to hex, the size of the buffer needed for the result is calculated as multiplication of the input length by 3. On 32 bit platforms, this multiplication may overflow resulting in the allocation of a smaller buffer and a heap buffer overflow.  Applications and services that print or log contents of untrusted X.509 certificates are vulnerable to this issue. As the certificates would have to have sizes of over 1 Gigabyte, printing or logging such certificates is a fairly unlikely operation and only 32 bit platforms are affected, this issue was assigned Low severity.  The FIPS modules in 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, 3.3 and 3.0 are not affected by this issue, as the affected code is outside the OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-31789\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libssl1.1\nVersion: 1.1.1w-0+deb11u5\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:11\nLink: [CVE-2026-31789](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-31789)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-31789**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | libssl1.1  | 1.1.1w-0+deb11u5  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:11  | [CVE-2026-31789](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-31789)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libssl1.1@1.1.1w-0%2Bdeb11u5?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian-11\u0026upstream=openssl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "0.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-27456-bsdutils",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-27456 medium vulnerability for bsdutils package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "util-linux is a random collection of Linux utilities. Prior to version 2.41.4, a TOCTOU (Time-of-Check-Time-of-Use) vulnerability has been identified in the SUID binary /usr/bin/mount from util-linux. The mount binary, when setting up loop devices, validates the source file path with user privileges via fork() + setuid() + realpath(), but subsequently re-canonicalizes and opens it with root privileges (euid=0) without verifying that the path has not been replaced between both operations. Neither O_NOFOLLOW, nor inode comparison, nor post-open fstat() are employed. This allows a local unprivileged user to replace the source file with a symlink pointing to any root-owned file or device during the race window, causing the SUID binary to open and mount it as root. Exploitation requires an /etc/fstab entry with user,loop options whose path points to a directory where the attacker has write permission, and that /usr/bin/mount has the SUID bit set (the default configuration on virtually all Linux distributions). The impact is unauthorized read access to root-protected files and block devices, including backup images, disk volumes, and any file containing a valid filesystem. This issue has been patched in version 2.41.4."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-27456\nSeverity: medium\nPackage: bsdutils\nVersion: 1:2.36.1-8+deb11u2\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:11\nLink: [CVE-2026-27456](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-27456)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-27456**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| medium  | bsdutils  | 1:2.36.1-8+deb11u2  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:11  | [CVE-2026-27456](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-27456)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/bsdutils@1%3A2.36.1-8%2Bdeb11u2?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian-11\u0026upstream=util-linux%402.36.1-8%2Bdeb11u2"
                ],
                "security-severity": "4.7"
              }
            },
